##Restaurant owners fight the plague: 14-fold increase in revenue from offline to online

From the challenge of doing business against the tide of the epidemic, to the large-scale ordering of free meals, to finding a new way to transform food and drink into food in self-help, in the restaurant owner's eyes, the epidemic once caused huge economic losses, also trained the team in the adversity of survival and innovation

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Create free meals for health care workers and others in the fight against the pandemic (source / interviewee provided)

By Zhang Yingxin, CAIJING correspondent

Editor | Yuen Man

What was your immediate reaction to the outbreak of NCP? A lot of people say, what should I do, but there are a lot of people, who don't have time to think from their own perspective, because behind them is the social life of the employee, the customer.

The outbreak spread across the country for more than a month, with the catering industry bearing the brunt of the impact. Many catering enterprises were forced to suspend business, but one restaurant boss said he had to from the perspective of employees, customers, social responsibility, obstinately "adverse" business. Some restaurant colleagues questioned him in the "stupid" , he insisted that he would not make unnecessary sacrifices.

Recently, this in the country has more than 100 stores, more than 10,000 employees, the outbreak of losses of nearly billion yuan of the catering business leader was interviewed by the "Caijing" reporter. He had just finished a video conference with the group at midnight.

"It's a lot busier than it was before the epidemic, " he said. Since the beginning of the epidemic, we have been on the forefront of the situation. I am afraid that if I say one wrong word or do one wrong thing, it will have a bad impact on the anti-epidemic work of our group. " He shared his "practical" experience in fighting the epidemic with the reporter from CAIJING, and stressed that "society needs us as long as we fight side by side. ".

Below is the person in charge of the catering business self-statement, "finance and economics" reporter carried out a partial deletion.

1. The war on disease: The challenge of doing business against the tide

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Anti-epidemic materials are in short supply in the early stage. Hubei area leaders use raincoats as protective clothing and provide free meals to frontline medical staff (photo source / Interviewees) 

Although he has led 10,000 employees through such emergencies as SARS and the earthquake in Wenchuan County on May 12, the new pneumonia outbreak is so severe that experience can not be copied, and "operational plans" can only be formulated according to specific circumstances. Our plan from the beginning to give up all closed shop or let the staff in place in the residence of the choice, but let the country more than 100 stores, can keep open business.

A restaurant colleague said, are you crazy, crazy? Such a query is normal, the epidemic in the catering industry suffered a huge impact, the loss of more than ten million yuan are not in the minority. On the basis of the economic losses, if we have to face the risk of new crown pneumonia infection, is undoubtedly worse.

I did the math, only 10 days after the outbreak, our turnover has dropped 80-90% compared to the same period last year, the refund of nearly 20 million yuan. I can't do the math. I can't live with the math. So this time, don't follow the "what do I do? " Line. So I asked myself three questions: What about the employees? What about the customers? Is there anything we can do to fight this?

Based on these three issues, our group headquarters quickly set up a prevention and control group, with me as the group leader, the president and the person in charge of quality control as the deputy group leader, and set up a four-level emergency prevention and control responsibility system of "headquarters, functional departments, regions and stores" , clear store is the prevention and control of the first pass, the first-line store manager is the first responsible person.

For the staff, we made specific requirements: 1, twice a day for the staff temperature measurement, and divided into three levels: dry cough, muscle soreness, systemic weakness need to leave; fever, dry cough need to leave; Body temperature above 37 degrees (hospitalised) and quarantined. 2. Upload to the BI system every day and monitor it. 3. Set aside an isolation room in each store for those with fever, cold, or discomfort. 4, the dormitory sends the Special Person Twice a day ultraviolet ray disinfection, and opens the window to ventilate, the depth sanitation is clean; must wear the mask, the glove and so on to go to work.

The problem of the staff is solved, the next step is the customer, the first is to ensure the safety of the dining environment. On the basis of the previous safety and health system measures, we have taken special measures from the Front Hall and back kitchen, such as disinfecting the floor of the Front Hall, door handle (once every hour) , public utensils, kitchen, etc.  Store head twice a day Will Be Watermark Camera Photo Upload Headquarters, everything can be tracked.

If the guests to the restaurant, we further request: to the hotel guests to take temperature, hand side disinfection; to provide customers with free disposable gloves, masks; to provide customers with dining spoon, public chopsticks; Table Space Open at least 1.5 meters; tableware is now placed, such as the guests are not assured of tableware, to provide once again hot tableware and other services.

Then there is the third question: What can we do to fight the epidemic?

"Food Service in peacetime, canteen in emergency period" , this is our experience accumulated in response to many sudden incidents. We have corresponding branches in Wuhan, Huanggang and other places in Hubei Province. We learned that the first-line medical staff needed to have meals. We immediately connected several key hospitals for the treatment of new pneumonia through the government. Starting from January 25, to provide free meals for front-line medical staff, etc. . In addition, we also to the community, sanitation workers and so on to give free working meals. At the end of January, we gave away more than 2,000 free boxes, and we continue to do so..

At the heart of all three is normal business, which was initially opposed by the government and others. Later, we communicated our real thoughts to the regulators. At this stage, the offline traffic and income were almost zero. We insisted that we did not open the store to make money, but want to be in the front-line medical staff, sanitation workers, such as free food. Then the government made an exception to keep us open.

There were some heartrending moments in the delivery process. Our own staff were in their early 20s, and meals were delivered to places that had been hit hard by the epidemic, and many of the deliverymen were in tears. What do we do? The head of the Hubei region took matters into his own hands, "being both a mother and a father, " donning raincoats without protective clothing to ensure that meals were delivered in time to where they were most needed. Later, the government sent us protective goggles, eye masks, protective clothing and other supplies, we are more at ease when delivering food.

2. Self help: from free food to mass ordering

Set up an off-line station to provide fresh food (source / interviewee provided) 

In fact, the operation of the war is also a self-help war, to support the anti-epidemic work, it must first ensure that they can survive.

Instead of giving our employees time off, we gave them triple overtime, gave them 2.2 million yuan in red envelopes to thank those who stayed on the front lines during the holiday season, and guaranteed their health, the cost of $380,000 worth of face masks, disinfectants, thermometers, alcohol, protective clothing... added to the other losses, if we don't find a way to save ourselves, we won't last three months.

The first challenge we face is how to digest the food? So, we started trying to open a convenient food station in the non-epidemic area. In addition to some inexpensive home-cooked dishes, there are also Huimin County dishes sold below market prices, such as Chinese cabbage at 2.30 yuan per catty, potatoes at 2.10 yuan per catty, white radish at 1.20 yuan per catty..

Very interesting, the line under the vegetable station revenue from the initial only a few hundred yuan, slowly rose to tens of thousands of yuan. At the same time, we have also opened online shopping applet, when users gradually feel the convenience of non-contact food delivery, have spread through wechat groups, friends tell more users, our customers continue to expand. At present, under the line convenient vegetable station highest daily revenue can reach more than 70,000 yuan, daily average revenue about 30,000 yuan.

On the other hand, the main takeaway has become our current inevitable choice. In order to reassure consumers, we further optimize the delivery process from the safety point of view. For example, the Front take-out counter has been added, and the take-out personnel try not to enter the store; the take-out personnel who come to take food also have to take food disinfection and body temperature measurements, and the packing personnel have to take temperature measurements, wear gloves and masks, and do a good job of tableware disinfection work. At present, our takeaway revenue in the overall revenue share has been as high as 80% .

We have also entered into cooperation with some retail enterprises to adopt the mode of "sharing staff" and central kitchen, so that our staff can provide sorting, preliminary processing, packing and other jobs for retail enterprises in our central kitchen, this can avoid our staff to go out, reduce the risk of staff infection. We now pack more than 100,000 bags of fresh vegetables a day for retail businesses.

It's worth noting that some business opportunities have made me more committed to what I do. In the early days, we asked our store staff to deliver free food to the community, the police station, the street and so on. We were very moved to do this, and then we began to order food in large quantities according to our needs: 20,50,200..

We give away our love, and we receive more love. In fact, I never thought of making money in this way, but business opportunities often appear at such times,

3. The Battle of transformation: A new approach to food

As more enterprises resume work, our work has also entered a new stage of development. We must make good use of this window period.

To make the transition work, more money is needed first. To be honest, the bank's support is limited. At most, it will allow you to defer your repayment. The slightly better ones will add a small amount of loan funds based on previous business transactions, but this will solve our cash flow problem, is a drop in the bucket.

Fortunately, the country has also seen our difficulties, all over the introduction of support measures for small and medium-sized enterprises, including tax relief, rent, to solve the problem of corporate financing and other difficult content.

On the day our company's city issued its support policy, I received a call from the relevant person in charge of the local commerce bureau, the heads of several commercial banks, financing and guarantee companies, and other institutions, the other side understood our difficulty in the fund in detail, and offered to provide the related fund support. Up to now, we have received loan financing support and loan approval from China Everbright Bank, Beijing Bank, Pudong Development Bank, Agricultural Bank, CITIC Bank, Minsheng Bank, Huaxia Bank and many other banks.

At that time, I have a very deep feeling, that is, as long as you do their own thing, many problems will be solved. We're short of money, and the banks are willing to lend, but only if you're really engaged in the fight against the epidemic, trying to keep yourself alive. After all, a bank can not trust you with its money if it does not see that you have the ability to do business and the sustainability of future growth.

Funds in place, based on the early planning, we continue to expand channels and products. Recently, we and a large supermarket chain cooperation, will open 4 new stores into the supermarket, each store about 20-30 square meters, to sell "semi-finished products" .

Early Research we found that consumers on hot lunch boxes, hot pot, cooked food and other semi-finished products in great demand, so we combine their advantages, semi-finished products to the supermarket to sell. At the same time, for example, for Kung Pao chicken, we will chicken with peanuts, onions, made into semi-finished products, and write the production process, customers buy home for a simple stir fry, edible. This, in fact, is the future of the restaurant industry -- as if it were a food business.

In addition, in recent years the relatively hot live broadcast also fully applies in our sales channel, even I, also is trying to do live broadcast. For example, we broadcast live on channels such as TMALL's flagship store, the chef taught fans how to make Tangyuan on the Lantern Festival through a live studio, and then tried many times to "Cook in the clouds" and so on, which indirectly boosted our food sales. At a recent TMALL event, sales at our flagship store rose 1,400 percent from a year earlier, from 0 p.m. to 7 p.m. on Feb. 17.

A lot of people ask me what I've learned from this outbreak? I think is to learn how to defend and self-help, in the process also exercise the team, train the team in adversity and the ability to survive and innovate. On the surface we did lose money, but we won the cohesion of our employees and the recognition of society, which is more valuable than money. Many restaurant owners later told me that they finally understood my earlier "obduracy" and praised me and all the employees.

In a word, when heaven closes a window for us, we should build a road for ourselves.

(Ma Zhongyuan, an intern at Caijing, contributed research.)
